{"books":{"63":{"id":"8994","title":"Leopard's Spots","description":"The first of Thomas Dixon's Ku Klux Klan trilogy that also includes The Clansman and The Traitor. Set in post-Civil War North Carolina (1865-1900), The Leopard's Spots weaves Dixon's impressions of the extreme social and racial tensions he witnessed during and after the Civil War, as Confederates attempted to fight off \"reconstructionist\" policy, restore order and rebuild the war-torn South, and sort out the rampant \"race question\" of the day, i.e., whether a leopard can change its spots? Characters include the villainous Reconstruction leader, Simon Legree (the very same slave driver from Harriett Beecher Stowe's Uncle Tom's Cabin, only 10 years later); Major Stuart Dameron, the book's hero and chief of the newly formed Ku Klux Klan; Charles Gaston, a young man who dreams of the governor's mansion; Sallie Worth, daughter of the old-fashioned south and a sweet-voiced idealist. A colorful assortment of carpetbaggers and emancipated slaves help round out the cast. (Summary by Michele T. Fry)","url_text_source":"https:\/\/archive.org\/details\/leopardsspotsrom00dixorich","language":"English","copyright_year":"1903","num_sections":"65","url_rss":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/rss\/8994","url_zip_file":"","url_project":"","url_librivox":"","url_other":null,"totaltime":"","totaltimesecs":0,"authors":[{"id":"10370","first_name":"Thomas","last_name":"Dixon, Jr.","dob":"1864","dod":"1946"}],"url_iarchive":"","sections":[{"id":"315184","section_number":"0","title":"Historical Note","listen_url":"https:\/\/librivox.org\/uploads\/rapunzelina\/leopardsspots_00_dixon_128kb.mp3","language":"English","playtime":"0","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"8463","display_name":"Michele Fry"}]},{"id":"315185","section_number":"1","title":"1.1 - A Hero Returns","listen_url":"https:\/\/librivox.org\/uploads\/rapunzelina\/leopardsspots_01_dixon_128kb.mp3","language":"English","playtime":"0","file_name":null,"readers":[{"